The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Blake bundled out by Simon
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Blake bundled out by Simon
                      
	Madrid: Frenchman Gilles Simon bundled American 11th seed James Blake out in the second round of the Madrid Masters on Tuesday.         
	Simon saved four break points in the second set and converted two of his own before dominating the final set to win 3-6, 6-1, 6-4.         
	US Open finalist Andy Murray moved into the third round when Simone Bolelli of Italy retired with an apparent shoulder injury while trailing 0-6, 1-2.         
	Murray will play Marin Cilic of Croatia, who beat Fernando Verdasco of Spain 6-2, 6-3.         
	Earlier, Finlands Jarkko Nieminen survived a fightback from Russias Mikhail Youzhny in their first round match to win 7-5, 3-6, 6-2. He next faces 10th seed Stanislas Wawrinka.         
	French Open semi-finalist Gael Monfils of France also advanced, beating Italian wild card Fabio Fognini 6-2, 6-4, while American qualifier Robby Ginepri defeated Michael Llodra of France 6-4, 6-4.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                      
